JO  - Management Science
SP  - 235
EP  - 247
VL  - 23
IS  - 3
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - A four-equation ?working version? system based on elements of a buyer behavior model was used to organize an analysis of a five-wave consumer panel tracking the introduction of a new brand of subcompact automobile. Parameters of endogenous model variables are remarkably stable over time, alternative brands, parameter estimation methods and specially-defined subgroups of the panel, while parameters of exogenous model variables vary systematically. The model behaves reasonably in a systems sense when tested with extreme values of endogenous and exogenous variables.
AB  - A four-equation ?working version? system based on elements of a buyer behavior model was used to organize an analysis of a five-wave consumer panel tracking the introduction of a new brand of subcompact automobile. Parameters of endogenous model variables are remarkably stable over time, alternative brands, parameter estimation methods and specially-defined subgroups of the panel, while parameters of exogenous model variables vary systematically. The model behaves reasonably in a systems sense when tested with extreme values of endogenous and exogenous variables.
